  "text": "If some idiosyncratic components are non-stationary, we can no longer use the EM algorithm described in the previous section. Indeed, when the residuals of (1) are non-stationary, the M-step estimator of the loadings cannot be obtained by regressing x it is I(1) onto f t and f t−1 . However, the case in which some idiosyncratic components are I(1) is the relevant one for large macroeconomic datasets, since otherwise all data would be cointegrated. This is, for example, shown by the empirical results in [CITATION_1] , where the methodology proposed by [CITATION_2] for testing for idiosyncratic unit roots is applied on a standard US macroeconomic dataset.",
